@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

@section outOfContainer{
    <div class="jumbotron">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Hello, world!</h1>
            <p>This is a asp.net core 2.0 project for Konusarakogren.com company interview. It includes parsing articles from wired.com and presenting it to signed users, who will choose one article and write related quiz questions for you.</p>
            <p><a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Quizzes" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" role="button">Check Quizzes Now »</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
}

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Parsing HTML</h2>
        <p>Using HtmlAgilityPack I managed to parse specific html codes from wired.com, and since html code could be changed, I've considered exceptions and tried my best for the application not to crash.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Using Code First</h2>
        <p>After understanding the scenario, I created the needed entities for the project, and using MSSQL to save data, It's possible to reach old articles and quizzes too.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Adding Ajax</h2>
        <p>For much easier and faster experience when enrolling to quizzes, after choosing answers for the specific quiz, the user can get the results at the moment!</p>
    </div>
</div>